ference-text">Paul's Alley was located 10 houses south of the <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Barbican_Estate" title="Barbican Estate" id="mwAjA">Barbican</a>. See p. 330 <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./James_Elmes" title="James Elmes" id="mwAjE">Elmes</a>'s (1831) <i id="mwAjI">Topographical Dictionary of the British Metropolis</i>.</span></li><li about="#cite_note-19" id="cite_note-19"><a href="./Michael_Faraday#cite_ref-19" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-19" class="mw-reference-text"><cite class="citation journal" about="#mwt53" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"Cite journal","href":"./Template:Cite_journal"},"params":{"author":{"wt":"Baggott, Jim"},"title":{"wt":"The myth of Michael Faraday: Michael Faraday was not just one of Britain&apos;s greatest experimenters. A closer look at the man and his work reveals that he was also a clever theoretician"},"journal":{"wt":"New Scientist"},"date":{"wt":"2 September 1991"},"url":{"wt":"https://www.newscientist.com/article/mg13117874.600-the-myth-of-michael-faraday-michael-faraday-was-not-justone-of-britains-greatest-experimenters-a-closer-look-at-the-man-and-hiswork-reveals-that-he-was-also-a-clever-theoretician-.html"},"accessdate":{"wt":"6 September 2008"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwAjM">Baggott, Jim (2 September 1991). <a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="https://www.newscientist.com/article/mg13117874.600-the-myth-of-michael-faraday-michael-faraday-was-not-justone-of-britains-greatest-experimenters-a-closer-look-at-the-man-and-hiswork-reveals-that-he-was-also-a-clever-theoretician-.html" id="mwAjQ">"The myth of Michael Faraday: Michael Faraday was not just one of Britain's greatest experimenters. A closer look at the man and his work reveals that he was also a clever theoretician"</a>. <i id="mwAjU">New Scientist</i><span class="reference-accessdate" id="mwAjY">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap" id="mwAjc">6 Se